# Architecture Rules

Apply when scaffolding or extending monorepos. Follow `.cursor/skills/architecture/` and `references/react-node-structure.md` for full layouts.

## 1. Frontend — Webpack Only

- **MUST** use **webpack 5** as the frontend build tool (`webpack`, `webpack-cli`, `webpack-dev-server`).
- **MUST NOT** use Vite, Parcel, Rollup, esbuild-only SPA tooling, Create React App, or Next.js for new frontends.
- React SPAs: `webpack.config.js` or `webpack.config.ts` in `apps/web/` (or equivalent app folder).
- Node APIs bundled for deploy: `webpack` + `webpack-node-externals` (see architecture skill Variant F/G).

```json
// apps/web/package.json — required scripts
{
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "webpack serve --mode development",
    "build": "webpack --mode production"
  }
}
```

### CSS Modules (css-loader v7)

When `apps/web` uses **CSS Modules** (`*.module.css`) with `import styles from "./X.module.css"`:

- **MUST** pin `"css-loader": "^7.1.2"` (or newer v7) in `apps/web/package.json`.
- **MUST** set `modules.namedExport: false` in the webpack css-loader rule (for `.module.css` or `modules.auto: /\.module\.css$/i`). css-loader v7 defaults `namedExport: true`, so the default export is CSS for `style-loader`, **not** the class map — causes `Cannot read properties of undefined (reading '…')` at module load.
- **MUST** name scoped files `Component.module.css`; global styles stay in `index.css` (no `.module` suffix).
- Full webpack snippets: `skills/architecture/references/react-node-structure.md` — **CSS Modules + css-loader v7**.

## 2. Root Folder & `packageManager` (Required)

- **MUST** create or update the **root** `package.json` (monorepo workspace root, not only app-level).
- **MUST ALWAYS** include `"packageManager"` in root `package.json` — never omit it on new or updated repos.

```json
{
  "name": "my-monorepo",
  "private": true,
  "packageManager": "npm@10.9.2",
  "workspaces": ["apps/*", "packages/*"],
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "turbo run dev",
    "build": "turbo run build"
  }
}
```

| Manager | `packageManager` value (use exact installed version) |
|---------|--------------------------------------------------------|
| npm | `"packageManager": "npm@10.9.2"` |
| pnpm | `"packageManager": "pnpm@9.15.0"` |
| yarn (Berry) | `"packageManager": "yarn@4.5.0"` |
| bun | `"packageManager": "bun@1.1.0"` |

- Pin the **exact** version (e.g. `npm@10.9.2`, not `npm@10`) so Corepack and CI use the same tool.
- When switching managers, update `"packageManager"` in the same change as lockfile / workspace config.
- **MUST NOT** ship a root `package.json` without `"packageManager"`.
- **npm / yarn classic / bun**: declare `"workspaces": ["apps/*", "packages/*"]` on root `package.json`.
- **pnpm**: add root `pnpm-workspace.yaml`; root `package.json` omits `"workspaces"` but **still requires** `"packageManager"`.
- Root scripts orchestrate Turbo: `dev`, `build`, `lint`, `test`, `preview`, `preview:stop` via `turbo run …` or `node scripts/…`.
- **`turbo.json` `build.env`**: list `PUBLIC_PATH`, `API_BASE_URL`, `NODE_ENV`, `PORT`, `API_PORT`, `WEB_PORT` so cache invalidates when they change. See `turbo-env-cache.mdc`.
- After changing `PUBLIC_PATH` on the CLI: `npm run build -- --force` then `npm run preview`.

## 3. Root `.env` — PORT, PUBLIC_PATH, API (Required)

All port and path configuration **MUST** come from the **root** `.env` (see architecture skill `react-node-structure.md` — Global Preview System). Commit `.env.example`; gitignore `.env`.

### Root `.env.example` (required variables)

```bash
# Single public-facing port (reverse proxy)
PORT=8080

# Asset + route prefix (/ for root, /myapp/ for subpath deploy) — path only, not a full URL
PUBLIC_PATH=/

# Internal app ports (preferred defaults — preview auto-picks free ports if busy)
WEB_PORT=3001
API_PORT=4000

# Base URL for React API calls (preview rewrites when API_PORT changes)
API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4000

NODE_ENV=production
```

### Wiring rules

| Variable | Used by |
|---|---|
| `PORT` | `scripts/proxy.js` — single entry URL `http://localhost:{PORT}{PUBLIC_PATH}` |
| `PUBLIC_PATH` | webpack `output.publicPath`, proxy static routes, SPA fallback |
| `API_PORT` | `preview-start.js` — probes `127.0.0.1`; picks next free port from `.env` preferred value (default `4000`) |
| `WEB_PORT` | webpack dev only (not used by production preview) |
| `API_BASE_URL` | Server-side / direct API access only. **Browser** `__API_BASE_URL__` in prod **MUST** be `PUBLIC_PATH` (e.g. `/qa/hello`), not `http://localhost:{API_PORT}` — so fetches hit `/{PUBLIC_PATH}/api/...` through nginx + project proxy |

### Preview `API_PORT` auto-assignment (Required)

`scripts/preview-start.js` **MUST** resolve a free **`API_PORT`** on `127.0.0.1` before spawning `apps/api` and `scripts/proxy.js`. Do not assume `.env` `API_PORT` is free.

| Port var | Default preferred | Auto-probe in `preview-start.js` | Used by |
|----------|-------------------|----------------------------------|---------|
| `API_PORT` | `4000` | **Yes** — scan upward to `9999` if busy | `apps/api` listen; `proxy.js` → `target` |
| `PORT` | `8080` | **Yes** — same probe as `API_PORT` (do not use `4001` in Docker; nginx uses it) | `scripts/proxy.js` listen; IM backend forwards `/qa/{name}` here |
| `WEB_PORT` | `3001` | No | webpack dev only |

**Algorithm** (inline in `scripts/preview-start.js` — do not require a separate `portUtils` package unless shared across repos):

1. Capture CLI `PUBLIC_PATH`, `PORT`, `API_PORT` **before** `loadEnv()`, restore after (CLI wins over `.env`).
2. `loadEnv({ rootDir })` — read preferred `API_PORT` from root `.env` / `.env.example`.
3. `findAvailablePort(preferredPort)` and `findAvailablePort(preferredApiPort)` — probe `127.0.0.1`; if busy, scan upward to `9999`.
4. Build shell env prefix: `PUBLIC_PATH='…' PORT={PORT} API_PORT={API_PORT} NODE_ENV=production` (escape single quotes in `PUBLIC_PATH`).
5. Spawn **api** and **proxy** via `spawn("sh", ["-c", `${envPrefix} ${shellCmd}`], …)` — **do not** pass a spawn `env` object; inline prefix wins over parent `.env`.
6. Write `{root}/.preview.ports` (`PORT=`, `API_PORT=`) and `{root}/.preview.pids`; log when bumped: `[preview] PORT 8080 in use → 8081`.
7. Log ready: `[preview] Ready → proxy http://127.0.0.1:{PORT}{PUBLIC_PATH} | API http://127.0.0.1:{API_PORT}`.
8. **Docker / IM platform**: project `PORT` is internal (`8080+`). Public URL: `http://localhost:4001/qa/{name}/` via nginx — never bind preview proxy to `4001`.

- **MUST** probe **both** `PORT` and `API_PORT` on `127.0.0.1` before spawn.
- **MUST** pass resolved `PUBLIC_PATH`, `PORT`, and `API_PORT` to both children via the shell prefix (same values for api + proxy).
- **MUST NOT** start preview assuming `.env` ports are free.
- Full script pattern: `skills/architecture/references/react-node-structure.md` — Global Preview System.

- **webpack**: `require("./src/config/env")` only — set `output.publicPath` from validated `env.PUBLIC_PATH` (never raw `dotenv` in webpack).
- **API calls**: inject `__API_BASE_URL__` with `DefinePlugin` (dev: `"/api"` via devServer proxy; prod: `PUBLIC_PATH` when subpath deploy).
- **preview scripts** (`preview-start.js`, `preview-stop.js`, `proxy.js`): use `loadEnv({ rootDir })` from `@repo/config/loadEnv`; capture CLI `PUBLIC_PATH` / `PORT` / `API_PORT` **before** `loadEnv()` and restore after so shell/CI wins.
- **API server**: read `API_PORT` from `@repo/config/env` (Joi default `4000`); never hardcode ports in source.
- Add to root `.gitignore`: `.env`, `.preview.pids`, `.preview.ports`, `preview-*.log`.

## 4. Preview Scripts (Required)

Every monorepo **MUST** expose production preview at the **root** so skills and agents can build, run, and verify the full flow on one port.

| Package manager | Root scripts |
|---|---|
| npm | `"preview": "turbo run build && node scripts/preview-start.js"`, `"preview:stop": "node scripts/preview-stop.js"` |
| pnpm | same script bodies; run as `pnpm preview` / `pnpm preview:stop` |

- Implement `scripts/preview-start.js`, `scripts/preview-stop.js`, and `scripts/proxy.js` from `react-node-structure.md` → **Reference — preview scripts**.
- Add `.preview.pids` and `.preview.ports` to `.gitignore`.

### 4.1 Preview runs in background (Required)

`npm run preview` / `pnpm preview` **MUST return to the shell** — do not block the terminal on the proxy or API process.

- **API** (and **web** if it has its own server): spawn with `detached: true`, `stdio: "ignore"`, then `proc.unref()`.
- **Proxy** (`scripts/proxy.js`): start as the **last step**, also **in background** (same detached pattern) — not `require("./proxy")` in the foreground.
- Write every background PID to `.preview.pids` (API, web if any, proxy).
- Resolve free `PORT` and `API_PORT` before spawn; pass both via shell env prefix (not spawn `env`).
- Redirect stdout/stderr to `preview-{label}.log`; `preview-start.js` exits after spawn (URLs printed, `main()` resolves).
- Full implementations: `react-node-structure.md` → **Reference — preview scripts**.

- **MUST NOT** use `stdio: "inherit"` or blocking `require("./proxy")` for the final server — that prevents background preview.
- `preview:stop` kills all PIDs in `.preview.pids` and frees ports from `.preview.ports` (fallback: `.env`).

### 4.2 Reverse proxy — API path routing (Required)

`scripts/proxy.js` **MUST** forward `/api/*` to the API with the `/api` prefix intact.

**Do not** mount the proxy with `app.use('/api', createProxyMiddleware(...))`. Express strips the mount path before the middleware runs, so `/api/v1/history` becomes `/v1/history` upstream and the API returns `404 Not found`.

**Do** gate API traffic explicitly (SPA fallback must not serve HTML for `/api/*`). Full `proxy.js`: `react-node-structure.md` → **Reference — preview scripts**.

| `PUBLIC_PATH` | Incoming request | Proxied to API |
|---|---|---|
| `/` | `/api/v1/history` | `http://localhost:{API_PORT}/api/v1/history` |
| `/myapp` | `/myapp/api/v1/history` | `http://localhost:{API_PORT}/api/v1/history` (via `pathRewrite`) |

- **MUST** verify proxied routes after preview start: `curl -sf "http://localhost:{PORT}/api/health"` and at least one `/api/v1/*` route (not only direct `API_PORT`).
- webpack devServer `proxy` with `context: ["/api"]` is unaffected (webpack does not strip the mount path).

### 4.3 Verify preview after work is done (Required)

When implementation is complete, **before** considering the task done:

1. Run `npm run preview` or `pnpm preview` (build + background start).
2. Wait briefly for processes to bind (e.g. 2–5s).
3. **Health checks** (retry with backoff if needed):

| Check | URL | Pass criteria |
|-------|-----|----------------|
| **API health** | `http://localhost:{API_PORT}/api/health` or `http://localhost:{PORT}{PUBLIC_PATH}/api/health` | HTTP `200`, body indicates ok |
| **Frontend health** | `http://localhost:{PORT}{PUBLIC_PATH}` | HTTP `200`, HTML/SPA loads (not 502/404 on `/`) |

4. If **either check fails** → read logs, fix code/config/build, run `preview:stop`, then repeat from step 1.
5. If **both pass** → work verified; run `npm run preview:stop` or `pnpm preview:stop` to clean up.

```bash
# Example verification (adjust PORT / PUBLIC_PATH from .env)
curl -sf "http://localhost:8080/api/health" || curl -sf "http://localhost:4000/api/health"
curl -sf -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" "http://localhost:8080/"
```

- **MUST** expose `GET /api/health` (or `/health`) on the API app for preview checks.
- **MUST** fix issues until both API and frontend health pass — do not skip verification.
- **MUST** always run `preview:stop` after verification (success or abandoned session) so ports are freed.

### Agent / skill flow

```
build → preview (background) → health API → health frontend
  → fail? → preview:stop → fix → repeat
  → pass? → preview:stop → done
```

## 5. Figma Design — `docs/figma-tree.md` (Frontend Only)

`docs/figma-tree.md` is the **frontend design index only**. It lists Figma file keys, screen links, node IDs, breakpoints, and routes — nothing else.

### Purpose & scope

| In scope | Out of scope |
|---|---|
| Frontend UI screens, states, responsive breakpoints | Backend APIs, database, server config |
| Links and node IDs already given in the project brief / PRD | Inventing Figma URLs not backed by the source file |
| Design tokens, component inventory, page map | Rewriting `docs/` requirements or test specs |

- **MUST** treat every Figma URL in `figma-tree.md` as the canonical target for that screen — implement frontend to match those frames.
- **MUST NOT** use `figma-tree.md` for non-UI work (API design, migrations, infra).
- **MUST NOT** delete or rewrite `figma-tree.md` during code-only tasks; update it only in an explicit **design phase** (or when the user asks). During implementation, **read** it — do not reshuffle links.

### Figma MCP (required before design & before frontend)

Connect via `.cursor/mcp.json` (`figma` server). Load `.cursor/skills/figma-design/SKILL.md` (and `figma-use` before any `use_figma` write).

| Step | MCP tool | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| 1 | `whoami` | Confirm Figma MCP is authenticated |
| 2 | `get_metadata` | Verify `fileKey` and listed `node-id`s exist |
| 3 | `get_design_context` / `get_screenshot` | Inspect layout, spacing, typography per screen link |
| 4 | `get_variable_defs` / `search_design_system` | Reuse tokens and library components when available |
| 5 | `use_figma` (write) | Create or update components and pages (requires write access) |

- **MUST** verify each link in `figma-tree.md` with MCP before building or updating that screen in code.
- If MCP is read-only, document the blocker in `figma-tree.md` and implement from verified screenshots/metadata — do not fabricate node IDs.

### Discover first — do not assume Desktop / Tablet / Mobile folders (Required)

**Before** creating or listing breakpoint rows, inspect what already exists:

1. Check whether `docs/figma-tree.md` exists and read listed links only — **do not** invent Desktop/Tablet/Mobile rows if they are not there.
2. Use Figma MCP (`get_metadata`, `get_design_context`) on the provided `fileKey` / `node-id` to see which frames, pages, and breakpoints already exist in the file.
3. Record only what is verified — one link, many links, or none.

| What the project gives | Agent action |
|---|---|
| **No `figma-tree.md` yet** | Create it in design phase with only verified MCP links from the source Figma file |
| **Single desktop (or one) frame link** | Treat desktop as **source of truth**; **auto-create** Tablet + Mobile layouts from it (Figma `use_figma` when write access, otherwise responsive CSS in `apps/web`) |
| **Desktop + Tablet + Mobile links already listed** | Use each link as-is — do not duplicate or replace |
| **Only marketing / reference frames** | Map the closest reference frame; note in `figma-tree.md` if app screens are code-derived |

- **MUST NOT** require a pre-built “Desktop / Tablet / Mobile” folder structure in Figma or in `figma-tree.md` when the brief only supplies one design.
- **MUST** derive responsive behavior from the desktop (or primary) frame when tablet/mobile links are missing: stack columns, shrink keypad, collapse side panels, touch targets ≥ 44px, breakpoints aligned with `test/*` or PRD.
- After auto-creating Figma frames (write MCP), append new `node-id` URLs to `figma-tree.md` in the design phase only.

### Design order — components first, then pages (Required)

**Do not** jump straight to full-page frames. Follow this order:

```
0. Discover            → read figma-tree.md + MCP metadata (what links/breakpoints exist?)
1. Tokens & foundations → colors, type, spacing (from Figma variables or reference frames)
2. Atomic components    → Button, Input, Display, Key, etc. (Figma components)
3. Composite components → Keypad, HistoryPanel, Shell (built from atoms)
4. Primary page frame   → desktop (or the single frame link provided)
5. Responsive variants  → tablet + mobile auto-derived ONLY if not already in Figma / figma-tree
6. States (optional)    → error / empty / loading when required by PRD
7. Update figma-tree.md → list only verified or newly created links (design phase only)
8. Frontend code        → apps/web; CSS/media queries for breakpoints missing in Figma
```

| Phase | Figma | Code |
|-------|-------|------|
| Components | Create/reuse **components** first | `apps/web/src/components/` mirrors component set |
| Primary page | Build from the **given** desktop (or sole) link | Base layout at ≥1024px (or PRD default) |
| Responsive | Add tablet/mobile frames only when absent | `@media` / layout rules for 768px and &lt;768px |
| States | Error / empty / loading when in scope | CSS/state classes |

- **MUST** create shared Figma **components** before composing **page** frames.
- Page frames **MUST** instance components (not detached one-off rectangles) when creating in Figma.
- Responsive pages are **generated from the primary design**, not copied from a template tree.

### `figma-tree.md` structure (minimum)

List **only** screens that exist or were created — omit Tablet/Mobile lines when not applicable.

```markdown
# Figma Navigation Tree — {App Name}
**File Key:** `{fileKey}`
**Prototype Base URL:** https://www.figma.com/design/{fileKey}

## Navigation Tree
[ENTRY] / → Screen name
├── [SCREEN] Screen — Desktop   → figma.com/design/...?node-id=...   ← source (required when provided)
├── [SCREEN] Screen — Tablet    → ...   ← optional; add only after MCP verify or agent create
├── [SCREEN] Screen — Mobile    → ...   ← optional; add only after MCP verify or agent create
└── [STATE]  Screen — Error     → ...   ← optional; PRD-driven

## Responsive note
<!-- When only Desktop link exists: tablet/mobile implemented in code; Figma variants TBD -->

## App routes ↔ test files
| Route | Context | Test file |
```

- Each listed line **MUST** have a full Figma URL with `node-id` verified via MCP (or marked as code-only responsive).
- **MUST NOT** paste placeholder `...` rows for breakpoints that do not exist yet.
- Map every entry to a frontend route and, when tests exist, a `test/*.md` file.

## Checklist Before Finishing Scaffold

- [ ] Frontend app uses webpack (no alternate bundlers)
- [ ] css-loader v7 + CSS Modules: `namedExport: false` on webpack css-loader rule; `*.module.css` + `import styles from "…"`
- [ ] Root `package.json` exists with **`"packageManager"` always set** (exact manager@version)
- [ ] Root `.env.example` with `PORT`, `PUBLIC_PATH`, `WEB_PORT`, `API_PORT`, `API_BASE_URL`
- [ ] webpack reads root `.env` (`publicPath`, `DefinePlugin` for `__API_BASE_URL__`)
- [ ] Root `preview` and `preview:stop` scripts + `scripts/preview-*.js` + `proxy.js` present
- [ ] `preview-start.js` probes free `PORT` and `API_PORT` on `127.0.0.1`; passes both via shell env prefix (not spawn `env`)
- [ ] `proxy.js` gates `/api` with explicit matcher (not `app.use('/api', …)` mount); listens on `127.0.0.1`
- [ ] Preview starts API + proxy **in background**; `preview` command returns without blocking
- [ ] API `/api/health` exists; preview verified (API + frontend health pass)
- [ ] `preview:stop` run after verification to free ports
- [ ] `turbo.json` at root with `build.env` for `PUBLIC_PATH`, `API_BASE_URL`, `NODE_ENV`; apps under `apps/*`, shared code under `packages/*`
- [ ] Checked `docs/figma-tree.md` + Figma MCP first — did not assume Desktop/Tablet/Mobile unless links exist
- [ ] `docs/figma-tree.md` exists — frontend-only index; only verified links (no placeholder breakpoint rows)
- [ ] If only desktop (or one frame) was given: tablet + mobile responsive layout auto-created (Figma and/or CSS)
- [ ] Figma MCP used to verify `fileKey` and each listed `node-id` before frontend work
- [ ] Figma **components** created before **page** frames (atoms → composites → primary page → responsive variants)
- [ ] `figma-tree.md` lists only real screens/states with URL + node ID (or notes code-only responsive)
- [ ] Frontend matches primary Figma link + responsive rules at 768px / mobile breakpoints
